description:
Hey there! I'm Carlos, a young business professional native from El Salvador. I'm currently pursuing my MBA at Simon Fraser University in Vancouver, Canada. I graduated Summa Cum Laude from John Brown University (Arkansas, USA) in May 2016 with a Bachelor of Arts in International Business, a Bachelor of Science in Marketing and Business Administration, and a minor in Leadership. I was recognized as the Highest-Ranking Graduate from the Soderquist College of Business (2016). I have been a scholarship recipient from: Beedie Family Graduate Scholarship (2020), Peter Legge Graduate Volunteer Leadership Award (2020), Walton International Scholarship Program (2012-2016), U.S. Department of State - Youth Ambassadors (2011), and Programa Oportunidades by Gloria de Kriete Foundation (2009-2011).

Upon graduating from college, I returned to my home country to work as a Marketing Analyst for Amway Central America and was promoted in 2018 to Sales Project Manager in Amway Latin America. I believe we all have a responsibility to leave a better world for the future generations, hence I have always been involved in projects and organizations (such as ENACTUS and the Youth Council for the U.S. Embassy in El Salvador) aligned to my passions - entrepreneurship, small business development, and youth empowerment ‚Äì as part of my giving back philosophy. I served as the Director of the 2016 Alumni Engagement Innovation Fund winning project for El Salvador, ‚ÄúJ√≥venes Pioneros‚Äù for five years. An organization born out of a $25K grant by the U.S. Department of State that promotes youth entrepreneurship through an innovative business curriculum designed for high school students. In February 2020, I was recognized as one of twenty ‚ÄúInfluential Youth from the Republic of El Salvador‚Äù for my volunteering endeavors.

In September 2020, I began my MBA studies online - given mobility restrictions - while I also joined local Salvadoran politics and ran for Congress as one of the youngest candidates for El Salvador's February 28, 2021 elections. Shortly after my participation, I was named National Youth Coordinator for the up-and-coming political party, Nuestro Tiempo on April 2021.

My future plans include advancing my professional career in business, continue contributing to the development of sustainable social impact projects, and continue my involvement in Salvadoran politics.

Feel free to reach out to me at carlose.lopezs94@gmail.com!

description:
Daniel Runde is a Senior Vice President at the Center for Strategic and International Studies and holds the William A. Schreyer Chair in Global Analysis, where he focuses on the role of using soft power to shape the future. A global thought leader, Mr. Runde has advised a number of governments including the United States, Japan, Denmark, Korea as well as the World Bank and the United Nations. He has testified before the U.S. Congress, and the Australian and Canadian parliaments.

In April 2018, Mr. Runde was named the Chair of the Advisory Committee for Voluntary Foreign Assistance, the Federal Advisory Committee that advises the Administrator of the US Agency for International Development and the broader federal government on international development issues.

Prior to coming to CSIS, Mr. Runde held senior roles and led organization change initiatives and built strategic partnerships at the World Bank Group and the US Agency for International Development. Mr. Runde is an Opinions Contributor at Thehill.com. He blogs occasionally at "Elephants in the Room" at ForeignPolicy.com. He writes and speaks extensively on global development issues. He was a member of the World Economic Forum Global Agenda Council for the United States. He currently serves on the board of the International Foundation for Electoral Systems (IFES) and the Ashesi University Foundation board, a Ghanaian university.

description:
I started out in digital media in 2006 as a Campaign Analyst as a part of SearchRev, a Palo Alto California based Online Advertising company. As a collective effort, we created online platforms, which are still in use in thousands of campaigns worldwide. I specialized in ROI target based optimization and conversion tracking. This was my first full-time job, and my passion for the field of modern advertising grew here.

SearchRev was then acquired by San Francisco based digital media giant AKQA and I was promoted to a Campaign Manager and ran performance based campaigns for companies like Shutterfly, Pandora, Verizon Wireless, HSBC, Ticketmaster while working from the El Salvador AKQA hub. At the AKQA El Salvador Hub I also led search, display, video and mobile campaigns for Coca-Cola LCBU Latin America from 2009 to 2011.

I was later on promoted to General Manager at the office and oversaw day to day management operations of the same office I developed. This included business financials and accounting, human resource management, direction, motivation and overall development and training of staff to ensure growth for the project.

I was then hired at White Shark Media to take the lead in the creation and direction of their search marketing efforts. Our main goal was the retention of our client base to ensure company profitability. With the aid of a well-trained team, we handle hundreds of clients ensuring that all processes were streamlined, coherent and up to par with client and market expectations.

After Developing Talent at my previous company and helping them to achieve a prestigious agency status, my entrepreneurial instinct kicked in, and with the help of our agency co-founders, we kick-started a Search Marketing Agency, Flame Tree Marketing. Flame Tree Marketing has grown to become a 50 person headcount agency, with numerous happy clients and high volume ad spend.

description:
What I know about you is that you are powerful. You are more powerful than you think you are, more powerful than you may be experiencing right now and even more powerful than you believe you can be. You are powerful!

It is my passion, purpose and joy to coach powerful women leaders when they have lost the connection to their innate power and are searching for how to reconnect so they can continue to make an impact in their career, be financially secure and have the time and energy to fully enjoy all of their life.

If you agree that this is you, then you know what it feels like to be moving through life powerfully. You‚Äôve had promotions, accolades, financial success and more.

However, you recognize that your life has changed. Maybe you have ended up in a job that is financially secure but emotionally draining. Maybe you lost out on a big project or promotion to someone younger than you. You may even be one of the 56% of people over 50 who lose their jobs before they are ready to retire.

You may also be experiencing changes on a personal level such as a change in a close relationship, a big move, physical trauma, children leaving the nest or parents aging.

There is no question that all of these changes can lead to stress, frustration and self doubt.

What I know with absolute certainty is that you can reconnect to your power. You can have the life you desire. And, you can have the best career of your life after 40, 50, even 60 and beyond.

I know this because I have been exactly where you are now and not only did I discover how to re-connect to my power, for 15 years I have coached 100‚Äôs of women to do the same.

I‚Äôm excited and honored that you took the time to read through my ‚Äòabout‚Äô page. If you recognize yourself on this page please reach out to me.

description:
Nelson Albareda, a Cuban-American business executive and GRAMMY¬Æ & Latin GRAMMY¬Æ Award winning producer, has over 25 years of diverse experience across media, live entertainment, marketing, content, sports and real estate.

Albareda got an early start in business at the age of 14 in 1990, where he became passionate about business and entrepreneurship. He had a successful career as a young professional, quickly moving up the ranks across multiple companies and diverse industries, including in the advertising, spirits, entertainment and media sectors. Initially starting at RMM Records (Universal Music), and eventually ending up at Univision Radio where he was responsible for creating the company‚Äôs non-traditional revenue initiatives across the organization.

In 2002, Albareda saw an opportunity in the events, entertainment and marketing space, which is where he had early success as an entrepreneur. Most notably in 2005, Albareda established Eventus, which grew to serve and partner with a wide-range of marquee clients such as Sony Music, Univision Communications, New York Yankees, Kimberly-Clark, Walmart, McDonald‚Äôs, Keurig Dr Pepper, HBO, Walt Disney Entertainment, Sirius XM and Latin GRAMMY‚Äôs among many others. In 2013, Eventus had become the largest multicultural marketing company in the US, which is when Albareda sold the company to Advantage Solutions via a roll-up strategy led by private equity group Apax Partners.

In 2017, Albareda established Loud And Live, where he currently serves as CEO. The company has quickly grown to be a dominant player across its areas of focus, including music, entertainment, sports, content development and marketing.

In addition to his endeavors at Loud And Live, Nelson has a real-estate portfolio and management company focused on commercial and multi-family properties in South Florida.

Albareda also has a long history of serving his community. In 2010, he was appointed by the US Congress to serve as a Commissioner on the Federal Commission to provide a report to President Obama on the creation of the National Museum of the American Latino in Washington DC. He also currently serves as a Member of the Board of Directors on the US Cuba Democracy PAC and F.A.C.E (Facts About Cuban Exiles).
headline: President & CEO at Loud And Live

description:
Who Am I...

For over 20 years, I have been a part of high profile, technology engagements while operating as an independent consultant, enabling business transformation through the integration of next generation, technically enabled solutions. I've been involved in projects that have represented pioneering solutions within Telemedicine and IoT.

My current work, as a technology thought leader, focuses around cloud-enabled, hyper scalable solutions, where I lead cross-functional project teams to solve business problems and create opportunities.

Over the years while working as a Lead Consultant for various Fortune 500 companies, not only my passion for technology has grown, but also my vision for the future of technology.

Skills & Passions‚Ä¶

Collaboration, Innovation, and Global Impact. I love to immerse in relevant technologies that bring about rapid and disruptive change. I give preference to those companies who have a noble mission statement.

I'm OK with highly difficult assignments.. Challenges with technology are not an if, but a when, and having the right mindset around meeting adversity allows for faster, more creative solution responses. Success is built on the back of failure because it is not about falling down but how you get back up.

Public cloud has opened up the possibility to innovate and respond faster than ever before. There are multiple open-sourced and defined technologies such as 5G, Blockchain, AI frameworks (TensorFlow, Pytorch), established AI models with trained data, that allow for fascinating creations that will rapidly evolve how we interface with the world.

Where Am I Going‚Ä¶

I'm particularly interested in how healthcare and smart cities will embrace all the technologies that I have touched upon, as well as new developments.
There is much opportunity given the connectivity of the 21st century to save many institutions their most valued asset, TIME.

It is my belief, and personal goal that we have the capability, through technology... to enable smart cities, be more productive with full self-driving cars, diagnose medical conditions faster, develop better drugs, create better understanding of our genetics to mitigate life threatening conditions, and expand our ability to engage in life in a deeper, more meaningful and productive way.

‚úÖ Through collaborative, innovative, and technology driven solutions, we can change the world!

‚úÖ If a digitally enabled future fascinates you, feel free to reach out to me via Linkedin email or DM.

‚úÖ Let's make the future happen now
